{
  "stem": "3097.2",
  "chunk_idx": 2,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 7.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 5,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "And he was also a supervisor in a movie, which belonged to the fourth regiment of infantry, which was stationed in our city.",
      "word_count": 23
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "So he was the supervisor, and we knew it.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "So the Kielce people used to congregate there.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I went to this [NON-ENGLISH] there.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 6,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And I used to make-- I used to make a few rubles by standing in the line and buying vodka-- because you couldn't buy any place else-- and then resell it, you see.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And over there, I met some other people who were thinking about going back to German-occupied Poland.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And over there I met Mr.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "Rubinstein, who's alive.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "He's here in Chicago.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "He met me there.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we decided to go back to the German-occupied area.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "We had to smuggle ourselves.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "It was winter.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "It was very cold.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "The snow was very high.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "But the [NON-ENGLISH] River, which was the border between the German and Russian-occupied area, was frozen.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And at night, we went, and we smuggled ourselves through.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And what happened-- we knew that everybody-- Jewish population-- everybody from about 10 years old-- had to wear a armband-- a white armband with a blue [NON-ENGLISH], OK-- a star of David.",
      "word_count": 32
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "We made ourselves those armbands in Lwow.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And when we came over the border, we were on a sled, and we put those on.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And on the way, we didn't realize that Gestapo, or whatever-- I don't know.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "The first time I saw those people with the bones, you know, and the, you know-- skull-- started to beat us up-- very bad with truncheons-- sitting on-- you know, we were sitting on the-- on the sled.",
      "word_count": 38
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they took us to the railroad station to unload the briquettes-- coal briquettes-- to put them in the truck-- on the wagons, you see?",
      "word_count": 25
    }
  ],
